s if the target platform ever changes."},{"body":"In `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` backoff path (~line 4634), after `preserve_interrupted_run(snapshot)` sets `snapshot.interrupted_run = snapshot.active_run.clone()`, the code then sets `snapshot.active_run = None`. Later on successful snapshot write, it restores via `snapshot.active_run = snapshot.interrupted_run.take()`. However, if the backoff sleep completes but the cancellation check at line 4714 fires, `fail_run_result` is called — but `snapshot.active_run` has already been restored (line 4711), while `snapshot.interrupted_run` was consumed by `.take()`. Verify that `fail_run_result` → `fail_run` → `preserve_interrupted_run` handles the case where `interrupted_run` is `None` (since it was already taken). The `preserve_interrupted_run` call inside `fail_run` will overwrite `interrupted_run` with the current `active_run`, so this appears safe. No change needed if confirmed.","rationale":"The snapshot state machine transitions in the backoff path are complex with multiple branches (snapshot write failure, successful sleep, cancellation). While analysis suggests correctness, the interaction between `interrupted_run`, `active_run`, `preserve_interrupted_run`, and the various error paths deserves explicit confirmation via a test that exercises cancellation during the backoff window."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"9d0cebc4-92d5-40d6-a8d0-267475e0d821"}
